WEBVTT

00:09.801 --> 00:12.762
I've heard one of the hardest things
to do in life

00:12.846 --> 00:15.473
is play an instrument
and sing at the same time.

00:15.807 --> 00:18.184
[strumming, singing] 

00:18.268 --> 00:19.102
[gasps]

00:19.853 --> 00:20.812
[splashing]

00:20.895 --> 00:24.524
[Drea] <i>Another really hard thing to do</i>
<i>is separate the art from the artist.</i>

00:24.607 --> 00:27.152
["DNA" by Kendrick Lamar playing] 

00:27.235 --> 00:29.362
It's especially hard when you're black.

00:31.364 --> 00:33.074
<i>We don't have as many icons,</i>

00:33.158 --> 00:36.244
<i>so it hurts a little more</i>
<i>when one of ours goes down,</i>

00:36.786 --> 00:39.247
but that's the thing about being black.

00:39.330 --> 00:41.499
You get used to things
being taken from you,

00:41.750 --> 00:43.460
which is ironic,

00:43.543 --> 00:45.754
seeing as we invented
the home security system.

00:46.755 --> 00:47.797
<i>Not that one.</i>

00:47.881 --> 00:49.507
-[barking]
<i>-Not that one, either.</i>

00:49.924 --> 00:52.802
<i>-Yeah, that one. The one with the buttons.</i>
-[beeping]

00:53.053 --> 00:55.722
<i>Hey, big ups to Marie Van Brittan Brown,</i>
<i>by the way.</i>

00:56.347 --> 00:58.433
<i>♪ Sex, money, murder, our DNA ♪</i>

00:59.601 --> 01:00.894
-[door closing]
-[Kenya sighing]

01:04.314 --> 01:05.440
[Kenya groans]

01:07.108 --> 01:08.902
Well, thank you for taking the time

01:08.985 --> 01:11.362
from your video shoot
to do this interview, Dad.

01:11.488 --> 01:14.240
Come on, you're a TV writer.
You look ridiculous.

01:14.324 --> 01:16.409
-You look like a blind drug dealer.
-Okay.

01:16.493 --> 01:17.577
Just...

01:18.745 --> 01:19.954
Please ask me your question.

01:20.705 --> 01:22.123
Such a hater, dude.

01:22.665 --> 01:24.501
-Fucking hater.
-Okay. So, Dad...

01:24.918 --> 01:26.628
-Yes.
-...I wanted to talk to you

01:26.711 --> 01:30.048
about how black people in this country
always seem to be on guard.

01:30.131 --> 01:31.341
It's because of slavery.

01:31.466 --> 01:32.926
-[Drea] Yes. I know that part.
-Okay.

01:33.009 --> 01:34.886
I'm trying to get to the bottom
of something else here.

01:34.969 --> 01:37.097
No, I know. Whatever question you ask me,
the answer's gonna be

01:37.180 --> 01:38.223
"because of slavery."

01:38.306 --> 01:39.933
So, yes, I can do this all day.

01:40.016 --> 01:40.850
Anything.

01:41.476 --> 01:44.229
You know what I'm saying?
Why do we like that? Why do we eat this?

01:44.312 --> 01:47.732
I can trace it back-- It's my North Star.
It's the thing that guides me in life.

01:47.816 --> 01:51.069
So, is the reason why you're wearing
a Mr. T level amount of jewelry

01:51.152 --> 01:52.153
because of slavery too?

01:52.237 --> 01:53.571
Such a hater. Yeah, hater.

01:53.655 --> 01:57.534
It's a Pusha T level of jewelry,
but yeah, it is.

01:57.617 --> 01:59.661
You know, our chains that we used to wear,

01:59.744 --> 02:02.288
remember those?
Those were made out of, like,

02:02.747 --> 02:04.874
fucked up, like, old...

02:05.625 --> 02:08.002
train tracks and shit.
You know what I'm saying?

02:08.211 --> 02:09.212
So now,

02:09.587 --> 02:11.756
they're made out of gold and diamonds

02:11.881 --> 02:14.008
and-- and rose gold.

02:14.092 --> 02:16.845
So yeah, so... take that, slavery.

02:17.512 --> 02:21.307
Wow, you're really trying to justify
spending my trust fund.

02:21.391 --> 02:23.309
Just tell me, is there anything left?

02:24.227 --> 02:26.146
You know what? Don't answer that.

02:26.229 --> 02:27.063
[cell phone chimes] 

02:27.147 --> 02:29.190
-Okay, just-- just humor here please.
-Okay.

02:29.566 --> 02:32.402
Is it just me or do people
in your generation

02:32.485 --> 02:34.445
really seem to look out
for one another?

02:34.779 --> 02:35.822
Um...

02:36.406 --> 02:37.365
Dad?

02:37.448 --> 02:39.659
-Oh, my God.
-Hello?

02:39.742 --> 02:40.618
Shit!

02:41.494 --> 02:42.996
They don't have it in my size.

02:45.582 --> 02:47.792
-I'm gonna buy it anyway.
-Are you shopping?

02:48.334 --> 02:49.169
Oh, my God.

02:49.252 --> 02:52.547
<i>And just like that,</i>
<i>I'd lost him, to a Mr Porter sale.</i>

02:52.630 --> 02:55.216
And who would shop low to high?
It's high to low.

02:55.300 --> 02:56.926
[Drea]<i> And in between him cursing the fact</i>

02:57.010 --> 03:00.430
<i>that they didn't have his size</i>
<i>in a Sacai velour-lined track pant</i>

03:00.722 --> 03:01.639
<i>and him wondering</i>

03:01.723 --> 03:04.058
<i>what the shoe conversion chart</i>
<i>was for the UK,</i>

03:04.976 --> 03:07.270
<i>I eventually just gave up.</i>

03:08.521 --> 03:10.857
That is, until he dragged me and my mom

03:10.940 --> 03:13.234
to an advanced screening
of a new black film,

03:13.401 --> 03:15.111
directed by a black director.

03:15.195 --> 03:17.447
[audience laughing]

03:20.783 --> 03:22.911
[Drea] <i>So the audience</i>
<i>clearly liked this movie.</i>

03:22.994 --> 03:23.995
[laughing]

03:24.078 --> 03:26.289
<i>And me and my dad clearly did not.</i>

03:26.372 --> 03:28.958
[mouthing]
What... the FUCK... is happening?

03:29.042 --> 03:30.210
[uproarious laughter]

03:30.293 --> 03:32.837
<i>♪ You either with me or against me, ho ♪</i>

03:32.921 --> 03:33.838
<i>♪ Ho ♪</i>

03:33.922 --> 03:35.757
<i>♪ You either with me or</i> ♪

03:35.840 --> 03:36.674
<i>♪ Wait ♪</i> 

03:36.758 --> 03:38.760
<i>♪ Win, win, win, win, win ♪ </i>

03:38.843 --> 03:39.719
<i>♪ Yeah ♪</i>

03:39.802 --> 03:42.764
<i>♪ Fuck everything else</i>
<i>Win, win, win, win  ♪</i>

03:42.847 --> 03:44.474
<i>♪ Win, yeah ♪</i>

03:44.807 --> 03:45.683
Let's go!

03:45.767 --> 03:47.518
Let's go, let's go now!

03:47.644 --> 03:50.563
-Crazy, right? I mean...
-That was so crazy. Crazy.

03:50.647 --> 03:51.481
[Joya] Whoo! 

03:51.564 --> 03:53.316
[muttering] Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

03:53.650 --> 03:56.069
-Yo! Game changer, right?
-Yo!

03:56.152 --> 03:58.029
Yeah, the game
has definitely been changed.

03:58.112 --> 03:59.572
-I mean, fucking fuck!
-Yeah.

03:59.656 --> 04:01.699
It was like a tour de force
of radical poignancy.

04:02.116 --> 04:03.952
-This was.
-A hundred percent.

04:04.035 --> 04:06.120
-Yes.
-Hey, Kenya, this is the type of film

04:06.204 --> 04:08.665
-people need to see right now.
-This... is.

04:08.748 --> 04:09.999
-A hundred percent.
-Yeah, one hundred--

04:10.083 --> 04:12.710
Everybody's so juiced
that you are doing the panel next week.

04:12.794 --> 04:15.088
-Everybody knows?
-Everybody. It's gonna be litty!

04:15.171 --> 04:18.341
-Litty. So every-- so everybody knows?
-[laughing] My guy!

04:18.424 --> 04:20.343
-A hundred percent everybody.
-Okay.

04:20.426 --> 04:23.179
So, the director of this film [bleep]

04:23.263 --> 04:25.848
asked my dad to introduce it
in front of an audience

04:25.932 --> 04:28.142
of peers, critics and fans

04:28.226 --> 04:30.561
and then, like, lead a Q&A afterwards.

04:30.812 --> 04:33.982
My dad agreed.
My dad agrees to everything.

04:35.191 --> 04:37.777
I just heard he's doing
a David Alan Grier biopic.

04:38.111 --> 04:39.988
It's basically the Buckwheat prequel.

04:40.071 --> 04:41.531
It's going down. You gonna be there?

04:41.614 --> 04:42.907
-Okay.
-My guy!

04:42.991 --> 04:44.075
We have to-- My guy.

04:44.158 --> 04:45.868
Oh. And if you've noticed,

04:45.952 --> 04:49.205
I'm bleeping out the names
of any actual artists or artists' work

04:49.539 --> 04:52.166
due to the fact
that my dad is in this industry,

04:52.250 --> 04:55.211
and it's how he takes care
of my mother and five siblings.

04:56.045 --> 04:58.881
Also, I hope to one day be
in the business myself,

04:59.048 --> 05:01.384
and I'd rather not have to change
my entire name.

05:01.467 --> 05:03.845
-Hey, hey, hey! Hit me.
-We-- No, my guy, we have to go right now.

05:03.928 --> 05:05.847
It's called <i>Lawyer, Wife, Mother of Six.</i>

05:05.930 --> 05:07.390
It got into Stedman's hands,

05:07.473 --> 05:09.809
so it's like one step away.
But I'll let you know.

05:09.892 --> 05:11.602
-I'll hit you up on DM.
-Okay. She will.

05:11.686 --> 05:13.521
-Why are you rushing me? Damn!
-[Kenya] We have to go.

05:13.604 --> 05:14.939
-We have that thing.
-[Joya] What thing?

05:15.023 --> 05:16.316
[Kenya] That thing we have to go to.

05:16.399 --> 05:18.026
You cannot do that panel, Dad.

05:18.109 --> 05:20.361
-I definitely can't do that panel, right?
-No.

05:20.445 --> 05:21.904
Wait, why can't you do the panel?

05:22.572 --> 05:24.741
-Did you see the movie?
-Yeah, I saw it.

05:24.824 --> 05:27.201
So, then you understand
why I can't do the panel.

05:27.535 --> 05:28.745
Okay, whatever.

05:29.704 --> 05:30.997
Wait, I'm sorry.

05:31.664 --> 05:33.207
Did you like the movie?

05:33.833 --> 05:35.793
Yeah, I liked it.
I thought it was good.

05:35.877 --> 05:37.879
[Drea and Kenya]
You thought it was good?

05:38.129 --> 05:39.964
I thought the cast was good,

05:40.048 --> 05:41.049
I liked the writing.

05:41.132 --> 05:42.925
[Drea and Kenya]
You liked the <i>writing?</i>

05:43.009 --> 05:44.552
Relax, okay?

05:44.635 --> 05:47.055
I don't watch movies
like you guys watch movies.

05:47.138 --> 05:49.807
-You mean lucidly?
-With the tiniest amount of discernment.

05:49.891 --> 05:53.102
No, with a giant stick up my ass.

05:53.186 --> 05:56.064
I watch movies for pure entertainment.
That's it.

05:56.147 --> 05:58.733
You look cute
and I'm so turned off by you right now.

05:58.816 --> 06:00.068
You know what I liked about it,

06:00.151 --> 06:03.363
is you just don't see black characters
in movies like that.

06:03.613 --> 06:04.530
Oh, my God!

06:04.614 --> 06:06.199
Dad, I just want you to know

06:06.282 --> 06:08.159
that when you guys split up,
I'm going with you.

06:08.242 --> 06:09.452
This is why you're my favorite.

06:09.535 --> 06:12.372
Okay, what was so bad about that movie?

06:13.164 --> 06:15.583
You know what, Par Par?
You wanna take this one?

06:15.666 --> 06:16.709
You know I do.

06:17.335 --> 06:20.505
Uh, first of all,
there was five characters named Bobby.

06:21.464 --> 06:23.966
<i>For the entire 25-minute Roscoe wait,</i>

06:24.050 --> 06:26.636
<i>I broke down everything</i>
<i>that was wrong with the movie.</i>

06:26.761 --> 06:27.845
Exactly.

06:27.929 --> 06:30.473
[Drea]<i> From the story being contrived,</i>
<i>to story holes,</i>

06:30.556 --> 06:33.226
<i>to plot points missed, to lazy direction.</i>

06:33.309 --> 06:35.895
<i>I think, at one point,</i>
<i>I said anyone involved in the film</i>

06:35.978 --> 06:38.398
<i>should be set on fire,</i>
<i>man, woman, or child.</i>

06:38.815 --> 06:39.732
[grunts frustratedly]

06:41.401 --> 06:42.777
-[Pops] Dad.
-[Kenya] What's up?

06:42.860 --> 06:44.487
-Can I ask you a question?
-Yeah.

06:47.573 --> 06:49.450
There's this girl at school, and...

06:51.411 --> 06:52.578
-[Kenya] Hold on.
-Never mind.

06:52.662 --> 06:53.538
No.

06:55.289 --> 06:56.124
Go.

06:56.707 --> 06:57.625
I want to hear it.

06:58.084 --> 07:00.837
Okay, so, there's this girl at school
and I really like her.

07:00.920 --> 07:04.924
Yo, Dad, you have to this.
[bleep] got a 99 on Rotten Tomatoes.

07:05.007 --> 07:06.592
Hold on. What? Oh, my God. Move, dude.

07:07.009 --> 07:09.262
Move! What's this? Look!

07:09.762 --> 07:12.181
-What is happening?
-I-- I don't know.

07:12.265 --> 07:13.766
A 99 for [bleep]?

07:13.850 --> 07:15.351
-Yeah. Okay, the consensus--
-Dad...

07:15.435 --> 07:17.019
-Dude. Fall back.
-Can you give me a second, bud?

07:17.103 --> 07:18.312
Please. Just one second.

07:18.396 --> 07:21.566
Okay. The consensus is that
it's a game-changing tour de force

07:21.649 --> 07:24.152
of radical poignancy
that America needs right now.

07:24.277 --> 07:26.028
What? [scoffs] 

07:26.112 --> 07:28.364
They're basically saying
it's a perfect movie.

07:28.448 --> 07:30.741
They're not basically saying it, Dad.
They're saying it.

07:31.325 --> 07:33.327
What-- What did <i>The Godfather </i>get?

07:34.162 --> 07:35.246
A 98.

07:36.164 --> 07:37.582
What did <i>Godfather II </i>get?

07:39.000 --> 07:40.084
A 97.

07:40.626 --> 07:41.794
Yeah, that makes sense.

07:42.170 --> 07:43.838
Hold on, what did <i>Heat</i> get?

07:44.630 --> 07:46.591
[inhales sharply]<i> Heat</i> got an 86.

07:48.926 --> 07:52.305
<i>Heat </i>got less than [bleep]?

07:52.388 --> 07:53.848
<i>-Heat?</i>
-Yeah. That's what I'm saying.

07:53.931 --> 07:58.561
A movie with maybe the greatest
ten minutes in the history of cinema?

08:03.524 --> 08:04.400
Go!

08:04.984 --> 08:06.027
What is going on?

08:06.110 --> 08:08.613
[Drea stammering]
I don't know. I have no idea. [sighs]

08:10.740 --> 08:11.949
-Dryan.
-[Pops] Dad.

08:12.366 --> 08:15.036
Bud, you got to give me a second.
Okay, bud?

08:15.119 --> 08:16.579
Seriously, I was winning anyway.

08:17.371 --> 08:19.665
Yo, have you seen [bleep]?

08:19.749 --> 08:21.334
Is your assistant on the line?

08:23.252 --> 08:25.630
Yo, man, between me and you,

08:26.005 --> 08:28.508
I have seen it and it is not it.

08:29.509 --> 08:30.510
Am I a hater?

08:30.760 --> 08:31.594
[Pops] Okay.

08:32.261 --> 08:33.095
Peace.

08:34.138 --> 08:36.307
[Drea] <i>So, while Dad tried to find answers</i>

08:36.557 --> 08:38.518
<i>Mom was stumbling into some questions.</i>

08:38.601 --> 08:41.229
[Joya] Oh, Stink! You look so cute!

08:41.312 --> 08:43.189
What's this?
"Five things I love about myself:

08:43.272 --> 08:44.982
hooper, sister,

08:45.149 --> 08:47.693
straight-A student,
sneaker enthusiast, boss."

08:48.277 --> 08:50.571
Well, you know where you get that from.
[laughs]

08:50.655 --> 08:51.489
Stink.

08:52.031 --> 08:54.158
Did you put "boss"
because you take after your mama?

08:54.742 --> 08:55.910
What are you the boss of?

08:56.577 --> 08:57.411
Right.

08:58.621 --> 08:59.455
Stink...

09:00.373 --> 09:02.083
I hate to be this person, but...

09:02.166 --> 09:05.545
did-- did you, I don't know,
maybe leave out a word

09:05.878 --> 09:07.630
that you would use to describe yourself?

09:08.506 --> 09:09.549
I don't know, what?

09:09.632 --> 09:10.967
You're black, sweetie.

09:11.551 --> 09:14.053
-Well, I mean, I guess.
-You guess?

09:21.352 --> 09:23.020
[Joya] What... what are you guys doing?

09:23.729 --> 09:24.689
We're dancing.

09:25.022 --> 09:27.817
-No, you are not.
-I'm doing the Orange Justice.

09:27.900 --> 09:29.569
I'm flossing, y'all!

09:29.652 --> 09:30.528
Me too!

09:35.992 --> 09:37.118
Fuck.

09:38.160 --> 09:39.745
I crippled my kids.

09:40.079 --> 09:42.957
Not only do they not identify as black,

09:43.499 --> 09:45.626
even worse, they can't dance.

09:46.961 --> 09:50.172
Not being able to dance
is worse than not identifying as black?

09:50.256 --> 09:52.842
Cut the shit, Drea. Okay?
I'm not in the mood.

09:53.634 --> 09:55.928
I know you forget this from time to time,

09:56.012 --> 09:58.556
but your mother is not 100% black.

09:58.639 --> 10:01.183
Mom, you're the blackest person I know.

10:01.267 --> 10:03.227
You're black
when you don't even need to be black.

10:03.311 --> 10:06.397
I've got a tall caramel frappe
for a Black Joya?

10:06.522 --> 10:07.440
Oh, that's me.

10:07.523 --> 10:10.067
[chuckling] That's mine. I'm Black Joya.

10:14.280 --> 10:15.114
What?

10:16.741 --> 10:18.284
You don't understand, okay?

10:18.367 --> 10:19.452
When you are mixed,

10:19.535 --> 10:22.330
you are constantly tested
on your blackness.

10:22.580 --> 10:25.082
How many pairs of bamboo earrings
do you have?

10:25.166 --> 10:27.168
What's your favorite episode of <i>Martin?</i>

10:27.251 --> 10:30.004
Name the Fab Five. Name the Jackson 5.

10:30.087 --> 10:32.131
Name the Central Park 5.

10:32.214 --> 10:35.009
Name all the members of the Wayans family.

10:35.635 --> 10:36.636
Do you know? No.

10:36.719 --> 10:38.888
It doesn't matter
'cause you're not mixed.

10:38.971 --> 10:40.514
Chick-fil-A or Popeye's?

10:40.598 --> 10:41.891
A.1. or Lawry's?

10:41.974 --> 10:44.560
<i>Can You Stand the Rain</i>
or <i>Can You Stop the Rain?</i>

10:44.644 --> 10:46.854
These are important questions.

10:47.313 --> 10:48.147
Whoa!

10:48.230 --> 10:50.316
Yeah, exactly, whoa.

10:50.483 --> 10:53.986
And if you know how to dance,
it gets people off your back immediately.

10:54.070 --> 10:55.488
That's currency.

10:55.571 --> 10:57.281
Can your mom dance?

10:57.573 --> 10:58.407
Sure.

10:58.532 --> 11:00.534
[hip-hop playing] 

11:01.661 --> 11:04.872
Can you also see her
mouthing the beat count?

11:06.082 --> 11:07.083
Also sure.

11:09.794 --> 11:10.920
That son of a bitch.

11:11.003 --> 11:13.172
He's talking shit about <i>my </i>dancing?

11:13.255 --> 11:15.257
[hip-hop playing] 

11:15.633 --> 11:17.677
Why does this bother you so much?

11:17.760 --> 11:20.596
Because he doesn't dance,
he does the two-step.

11:20.680 --> 11:22.264
He just goes from one side to another--

11:22.348 --> 11:25.309
Not the two-step, Mom.
The fact that your kids can't dance.

11:25.393 --> 11:27.770
Because I am their mother.

11:27.853 --> 11:31.273
Okay? And it is my job
to send them out into the world

11:31.357 --> 11:33.984
with a toolbox filled
with things that they will need

11:34.068 --> 11:35.695
and they could pull out
whenever they want,

11:35.778 --> 11:38.322
and this is currency. They need currency.

11:38.406 --> 11:39.615
Do you know what I'm saying?

11:39.699 --> 11:42.034
I-- I think you just said
what you're saying.

11:42.118 --> 11:45.204
So you get that they need things
in their toolbox right now.

11:45.287 --> 11:46.288
They need currency...

11:46.372 --> 11:47.873
-I got it, Mom. I got it.
-...to pull out.

11:47.957 --> 11:50.084
I want them to have that in there
so they can pull it out when they need it.

11:50.167 --> 11:51.419
Okay, crazy!

11:53.003 --> 11:55.256
[Kenya] <i>Space Jam </i>got a 35%.

11:55.923 --> 11:57.341
Can you believe this shit?

11:58.175 --> 11:59.051
[Joya] Kenya.

12:00.302 --> 12:01.637
We have a problem.

12:01.721 --> 12:04.306
Yeah, with <i>Space Jam, </i>35%.

12:04.515 --> 12:07.101
Michael Jordan fighting aliens, 35%.
<i>Top Gun?</i>

12:07.727 --> 12:10.646
Fifty-five percent.
Maverick, Goose, Goose dies.

12:11.188 --> 12:14.233
No. No, no, no.
We-- We're having a barbecue.

12:14.316 --> 12:16.360
-We have to have a barbecue.
-Okay.

12:16.444 --> 12:17.903
Okay? A black barbecue.

12:17.987 --> 12:20.030
-What?
-With just your family.

